<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10006] @CompileStatic fails to unify types</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10006</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-groovy&quot;&gt;
@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A {
    static &amp;lt;U&amp;gt; void foo(U a, U b) {}

    static void main(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;[] args) {
        foo(1, &quot;&quot;)
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following code fails to compile with error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Groovyc: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Static type checking&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; - Cannot call &amp;lt;U&amp;gt; A#foo(U, U) with arguments &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;int, java.lang.String&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt; &lt;tt&gt;U&lt;/tt&gt; should be inferred to LUB(Integer, String), hence the call should be successful.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
